<@U2670DYLE|johncohoon> commented on <@U2670DYLE|johncohoon>’s file <https://uncorked.slack.com/files/johncohoon/F5P2F8ETS/screen_shot_2017-06-06_at_4.42.47_pm.png|Updated 3D Earth Urls>: <@U0U9WJB7F> You can test it with postman(<https://www.getpostman.com/>) You can enter this endpoint: <https://gweb-uncorked-3pr.appspot.com/api/earth/get_random_images>
Then in the headers section, you need to add X-3PR-Security with the value da39a3ee5e6b4b0d3255bfef95601890afd80709 as shown in the screenshot from above.

This endpoint returns 10 random images with urls for the static image, the earth link, and lat long.

To check that things are looking the way they should, you can load the earth_3d_link in a browser and then the image_link and make sure they match up.

You can also browse the datastore, here: <https://console.cloud.google.com/datastore/entities/query?project=gweb-uncorked-3pr&ns=&kind=EarthImage>
